instructions: Slice the fish into 1-inch thick strips. Heat oil in a medium saucepan to 350F. Combine flour, baking powder, and salt in a medium bowl. Pour in the beer (or milk) and mix until smooth. Dip one piece of fish into the batter and coat. Transfer to hot oil. Repeat with 3 or 4 more pieces and fry until golden (4 minutes or so). Dont crowd the pot too much or the temperature of the oil will drop too much. Remove the fish from the oil and set on a cooling rack. Serve with warm corn tortillas (or pan fry the tortillas if youre feeling decadent), cabbage, salsa, and lime.November 13th, 2008: 8:54 pmfiled under booze, dinner, recipes, savory, seafood

steps.step: Slice the fish into 1-inch thick strips.
Heat oil in a medium saucepan to 350F.
Combine flour, baking powder, and salt in a medium bowl.
Pour in the beer (or milk) and mix until smooth. Dip one piece of fish into the batter and coat.
Transfer to hot oil. Repeat with 3 or 4 more pieces and fry until golden (4 minutes or so). Dont crowd the pot too much or the temperature of the oil will drop too much.
Remove the fish from the oil and set on a cooling rack.
Serve with warm corn tortillas (or pan fry the tortillas if youre feeling decadent), cabbage, salsa, and lime.November 13th, 2008: 8:54 pmfiled under booze, dinner, recipes, savory, seafood
